    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Take your<strong> chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Deseed your<strong> pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and chop roughly</p><p>Peel and finely dice your <strong>shallot[s]</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-chicken-and-pepper-wholewheat-pasta-bake/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced shallot</strong>, <strong>chopped pepper</strong> and<strong> diced chicken breast</strong> and cook for an initial 5-6 min</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-chicken-and-pepper-wholewheat-pasta-bake/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>pasta </strong>to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the <strong>pasta </strong>for 7-9 min (10-12 min for wholewheat)</p><p>Tip: It doesn't need to be fully cooked, as it will go in the oven later!</p><p>Once done, drain the<strong> pasta</strong>, reserving a cup of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-chicken-and-pepper-wholewheat-pasta-bake/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix </strong>with your <strong>tomato paste</strong> in 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[275ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[350ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> \u2013 this is your<strong> tomato stock</strong></p><p>After an initial 5-6 min, add the<strong> chopped garlic </strong>and <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong> to the pan with your<strong> cayenne pepper</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and 2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and cook for 1-2 min further or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-chicken-and-pepper-wholewheat-pasta-bake/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add the<strong> tomato stock</strong> and <strong>soured cream</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Season with a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and<strong> pepper </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until the sauce has slightly thickened and the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your<strong> smoky sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-chicken-and-pepper-wholewheat-pasta-bake/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-chicken-and-pepper-wholewheat-pasta-bake/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>cooked pasta </strong>and a splash of <strong>starchy pasta water</strong> to the smoky sauce and stir it all together until the pasta is fully coated in the sauce</p><p>Transfer the mixture to an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong> and top with the <strong>grated cheese</strong></p><p>Put the dish in the oven for 10 min or until the cheese has melted \u2013 this is your <strong>smoky chicken & pepper pasta bake</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-chicken-and-pepper-wholewheat-pasta-bake/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve your <strong>smoky chicken & pepper pasta bake </strong>and season with a grind of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
